#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:2
msgid "Defining worlds, robots, and sensors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:4
msgid ""
"**Goal:** Learn the basics of defining MVSim world files, adding vehicles "
"and sensors, and the main features available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:6
msgid "**Tutorial level:** Advanced"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:8
msgid "**Time:** 30 minutes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:12
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:15
msgid "Background"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:17
msgid ""
"MVSim worlds are defined in XML files (``.world.xml``). A world file "
"describes the environment (ground, walls, obstacles), the vehicles (dynamics "
"model, shape, sensors), and simulation parameters (physics timestep, GUI "
"options)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:21
msgid ""
"MVSim provides a library of predefined vehicle and sensor definitions that "
"you can reuse in your worlds via XML includes. You can also define "
"everything from scratch for full control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:25
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:27
msgid ""
"You should have completed the :doc:`Getting-Started-MVSim` tutorial and have "
"MVSim installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:30
msgid "Tasks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:33
msgid "1 Minimal world file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:35
msgid ""
"Here is a minimal world file that creates an empty environment with one "
"robot:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:37
msgid ""
"<mvsim_world version=\"1.0\">\n"
"  <!-- Simulation settings -->\n"
"  <simul_timestep>5e-3</simul_timestep>\n"
"\n"
"  <!-- GUI options -->\n"
"  <gui>\n"
"      <cam_distance>15</cam_distance>\n"
"  </gui>\n"
"\n"
"  <!-- Ground plane -->\n"
"  <element class=\"ground_grid\">\n"
"  </element>\n"
"\n"
"  <!-- A differential-drive robot -->\n"
"  <vehicle name=\"robot1\">\n"
"    <init_pose>0 0 0</init_pose>  <!-- x y yaw(deg) -->\n"
"\n"
"    <!--  Dynamical model -->\n"
"    <dynamics class=\"differential\">\n"
"        <!-- Params -->\n"
"        <l_wheel pos=\"0.0  0.5\" mass=\"4.0\" width=\"0.20\" "
"diameter=\"0.40\" />\n"
"        <r_wheel pos=\"0.0 -0.5\" mass=\"4.0\" width=\"0.20\" "
"diameter=\"0.40\" />\n"
"\n"
"        <!-- Visual and physical shape -->\n"
"        <chassis mass=\"15.0\" zmin=\"0.05\" zmax=\"0.6\">\n"
"        </chassis>\n"
"\n"
"        <!--   Motor controller -->\n"
"        <controller class=\"twist_pid\">\n"
"            <!-- Params -->\n"
"            <KP>4.1543</KP>\n"
"            <KI>1.9118</KI>\n"
"            <KD>0.0000</KD>\n"
"            <max_torque>14.44</max_torque>\n"
"            <V>0.0</V><W>0</W>\n"
"        </controller>\n"
"    </dynamics>\n"
"\n"
"    <!-- Motor controller: accept twist commands, PID controller -->\n"
"    <controller class=\"twist_pid\">\n"
"      <KP>100</KP> <KI>5</KI> <max_torque>50</max_torque>\n"
"    </controller>\n"
"  </vehicle>\n"
"</mvsim_world>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:84
msgid "Save this as ``my_world.world.xml`` and launch it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:86
msgid "$ mvsim launch my_world.world.xml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:91
msgid "2 Using predefined vehicles and sensors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:93
msgid ""
"Instead of defining vehicles from scratch, you can use the predefined "
"definitions that ship with MVSim. These are XML files in the ``definitions/"
"`` directory of the MVSim package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:96
msgid "**Available vehicles:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:98
msgid ""
"``turtlebot3_burger.vehicle.xml`` -- TurtleBot3 Burger (differential drive)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:99
msgid "``jackal.vehicle.xml`` -- Clearpath Jackal UGV (4-wheel differential)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:100
msgid "``ackermann.vehicle.xml`` -- Generic Ackermann (car-like) vehicle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:101
msgid "``pickup.vehicle.xml`` -- Pickup truck (Ackermann)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:102
msgid ""
"``agricobiot2.vehicle.xml`` -- Agricultural robot (Ackermann drivetrain)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:104
msgid "**Available sensors:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:106
msgid "``lidar2d.sensor.xml`` -- Generic 2D laser scanner"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:107
msgid "``rplidar-a2.sensor.xml`` -- RPLidar A2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:108
msgid "``velodyne-vlp16.sensor.xml`` -- Velodyne VLP-16 3D LiDAR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:109
msgid "``ouster-os1.sensor.xml`` -- Ouster OS1 3D LiDAR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:110
msgid "``helios-32-FOV-70.sensor.xml`` -- Helios 32-beam 3D LiDAR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:111
msgid "``camera.sensor.xml`` -- RGB camera"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:112
msgid "``rgbd_camera.sensor.xml`` -- Depth camera (RGBD)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:113
msgid "``imu.sensor.xml`` -- Inertial measurement unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:114
msgid "``gnss.sensor.xml`` -- GPS/GNSS receiver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:116
msgid "To use a predefined vehicle with sensors attached, use XML includes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:118
msgid ""
"<mvsim_world version=\"1.0\">\n"
"  <simul_timestep>5e-3</simul_timestep>\n"
"\n"
"  <gui>\n"
"      <cam_distance>15</cam_distance>\n"
"  </gui>\n"
"\n"
"  <element class=\"ground_grid\">\n"
"  </element>\n"
"\n"
"  <!-- Include the Jackal vehicle definition -->\n"
"  <include file=\"$(ros2 pkg prefix mvsim)/share/mvsim/definitions/jackal."
"vehicle.xml\"\n"
"    default_sensors=\"true\"\n"
"    />\n"
"\n"
"  <vehicle name=\"r1\" class=\"jackal\">\n"
"    <init_pose>0 0 170</init_pose>  <!-- In global coords: x,y, yaw(deg) --"
">\n"
"    <init_vel>0 0 0</init_vel>  <!-- In local coords: vx,vy, omega(deg/s) --"
">\n"
"\n"
"    <!-- You can also attach sensors to vehicles in separate includes,\n"
"        or define them inline within the vehicle block. -->\n"
"    <!-- <include file=\"$(ros2 pkg prefix mvsim)/share/mvsim/definitions/"
"lidar2d.sensor.xml\" sensor_x=\"1.7\" sensor_z=\"1.01\" sensor_yaw=\"0\" "
"max_range=\"70.0\" sensor_name=\"laser1\" />  -->\n"
"  </vehicle>\n"
"\n"
"  <variable name=\"WALL_THICKNESS\" value=\"0.2\"></variable>\n"
"\n"
"  <!-- Wall with a single door -->\n"
"  <element class=\"vertical_plane\">\n"
"    <x0>-10</x0> <y0>-10</y0>\n"
"    <x1>-10</x1> <y1>10</y1>\n"
"    <z>0.0</z> <height>3.0</height>\n"
"    <cull_face>NONE</cull_face>\n"
"    <texture>https://mrpt.github.io/mvsim-models/textures-cgbookcase/wall-"
"bricks-01.png</texture>\n"
"    <texture_size_x>2.5</texture_size_x>\n"
"    <texture_size_y>2.5</texture_size_y>\n"
"    <thickness>${WALL_THICKNESS}</thickness>  <!-- Wall thickness in meters "
"-->\n"
"\n"
"    <!-- Door at 50% position (middle of wall), 1.2m wide, standard height --"
">\n"
"    <door>\n"
"      <position>0.5</position>  <!-- 0.0 = start point, 1.0 = end point -->\n"
"      <width>1.2</width>        <!-- meters -->\n"
"      <z_min>0.0</z_min>        <!-- bottom of door -->\n"
"      <z_max>2.1</z_max>        <!-- top of door -->\n"
"      <name>main_entrance</name>\n"
"    </door>\n"
"  </element>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"</mvsim_world>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:171
msgid "3 World environment elements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:173
msgid "MVSim supports several types of environment elements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:175
msgid ""
"**Occupancy grid maps** load a grayscale image as a 2D obstacle map, "
"commonly used for indoor navigation testing:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:177
msgid ""
"<element class=\"occupancy_grid\">\n"
"  <file>map.png</file>\n"
"  <resolution>0.05</resolution>  <!-- meters/pixel -->\n"
"</element>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:184
msgid ""
"**Elevation maps** define terrain height from a grayscale heightmap image, "
"useful for outdoor scenarios:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:186
msgid ""
"<element class=\"elevation_map\">\n"
"  <resolution>1.0</resolution>\n"
"  <elevation_image>terrain.png</elevation_image>\n"
"  <elevation_image_min_z>0.0</elevation_image_min_z>\n"
"  <elevation_image_max_z>5.0</elevation_image_max_z>\n"
"</element>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:195
msgid "**Textured planes** add visual ground surfaces:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:197
msgid ""
"<element class=\"horizontal_plane\">\n"
"  <cull_face>BACK</cull_face>\n"
"  <x_min>-25</x_min> <x_max>25</x_max>\n"
"  <y_min>-25</y_min> <y_max>25</y_max>\n"
"  <z>0.0</z>\n"
"  <texture>asphalt.png</texture>\n"
"  <texture_size_x>5.0</texture_size_x>\n"
"  <texture_size_y>5.0</texture_size_y>\n"
"</element>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:209
msgid ""
"**Blocks** are static or dynamic rigid bodies (boxes, custom shapes) that "
"serve as obstacles or manipulable objects:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:211
msgid ""
"<block class=\"obstacle1\">\n"
"  <shape_from_visual/>\n"
"  <visual>\n"
"    <model_uri>package://mvsim/models/box.dae</model_uri>\n"
"  </visual>\n"
"  <init_pose>3.0 2.0 0</init_pose>\n"
"  <mass>20</mass>\n"
"</block>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:223
msgid "4 Vehicle dynamics models"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:225
msgid "MVSim provides three main dynamics models:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:227
msgid ""
"**Differential drive** (``class=\"differential\"``): Two-wheeled robots like "
"TurtleBot3. Controlled via linear and angular velocity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:230
msgid ""
"**Ackermann** (``class=\"ackermann\"``): Car-like vehicles with front-wheel "
"steering. Controlled via linear velocity and steering angle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:233
msgid ""
"**Ackermann drivetrain** (``class=\"ackermann_drivetrain\"``): Realistic "
"drivetrain model with open or Torsen differentials, useful for more accurate "
"vehicle behavior simulation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:236
msgid "Each vehicle can use different motor controllers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:238
msgid ""
"``twist_pid``: Accepts ``geometry_msgs/msg/Twist`` commands with PID "
"velocity tracking. This is the most common choice for ROS 2 integration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:240
msgid "``twist_ideal``: Instantaneous velocity commands (no dynamics delay)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:241
msgid ""
"``twist_front_steer_pid``: For Ackermann vehicles controlled via linear "
"velocity and steering angle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:242
msgid "``raw``: Direct wheel torque control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:245
msgid "5 Sensor noise and configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:247
msgid ""
"Sensors in MVSim support configurable noise models. For example, an IMU "
"sensor with noise parameters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:250
msgid ""
"<sensor class=\"imu\" name=\"imu1\">\n"
"  <pose>0 0 0.5 0 0 0</pose>  <!-- x y z roll pitch yaw -->\n"
"  <rate_hz>100</rate_hz>\n"
"\n"
"  <!-- Gyroscope noise -->\n"
"  <gyroscope_noise>\n"
"    <noise_std>1e-3</noise_std>           <!-- rad/s -->\n"
"    <bias_initial_std>1e-4</bias_initial_std>\n"
"    <bias_drift>1e-6</bias_drift>\n"
"  </gyroscope_noise>\n"
"\n"
"  <!-- Accelerometer noise -->\n"
"  <accelerometer_noise>\n"
"    <noise_std>1e-2</noise_std>           <!-- m/s^2 -->\n"
"    <bias_initial_std>1e-3</bias_initial_std>\n"
"    <bias_drift>1e-5</bias_drift>\n"
"  </accelerometer_noise>\n"
"</sensor>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:271
msgid ""
"LiDAR sensors support parameters for range, angular resolution, and noise:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:273
msgid ""
"<sensor class=\"laser\" name=\"laser1\">\n"
"  <pose>0.15 0 0.3 0 0 0</pose>\n"
"  <rate_hz>10</rate_hz>\n"
"  <ray_count>360</ray_count>\n"
"  <fov_degrees>360</fov_degrees>\n"
"  <range_max>20.0</range_max>\n"
"  <range_std_noise>0.01</range_std_noise>  <!-- meters -->\n"
"  <raytrace_3d>true</raytrace_3d>  <!-- use 3D collision for 2D scans -->\n"
"</sensor>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:286
msgid "6 Additional features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:288
msgid ""
"**Multi-robot simulation:** MVSim natively supports multiple vehicles in the "
"same world. Each vehicle gets its own ROS 2 namespace, TF tree, and set of "
"topics. Robots can detect each other with their sensors and physically "
"interact through collisions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:293
msgid ""
"**Property regions:** You can define regions in the world with different "
"physical properties, such as varying friction coefficients or GPS-denied "
"zones where GNSS sensors stop reporting positions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:297
msgid ""
"**Animated actors:** MVSim supports skeletal-animated 3D characters (e.g., "
"pedestrians) that follow waypoint paths, useful for testing perception and "
"planning in dynamic environments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:301
msgid ""
"**Joints and articulated vehicles:** Vehicles can be connected using "
"distance joints (ropes/cables) or revolute joints (hinges), enabling "
"simulation of trailers, tow ropes, and articulated systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:305
msgid ""
"**XML advanced features:** World files support ``<include>`` directives, "
"variable substitution, mathematical expressions, ``<for>`` loops, and "
"``<if>`` conditionals, making it possible to procedurally generate complex "
"environments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:309
msgid ""
"**Headless and faster-than-real-time:** MVSim can run without a GUI and at "
"configurable simulation speed, which is useful for automated testing and "
"reinforcement learning workflows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:314
msgid "Comparison with other simulators"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:316
msgid "MVSim occupies a different niche compared to other simulators:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:318
msgid "**Strengths:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:320
msgid "Very lightweight: low CPU and memory usage, fast startup times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:321
msgid "Focused vehicle dynamics with multiple friction and drivetrain models."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:322
msgid "Simple XML-based world format, easy to get started."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:323
msgid "Native multi-robot support with per-vehicle ROS 2 namespaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:324
msgid "Faster-than-real-time simulation for batch testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:325
msgid "Procedural world generation via XML loops and conditionals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:327
msgid "**Limitations:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:329
msgid ""
"Physics is 2D (Box2D): no full 3D rigid body dynamics. Objects do not tip "
"over or fly. Elevation maps add terrain height but the physics remains "
"fundamentally 2D."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:332
msgid ""
"Sensor simulation is less detailed than full 3D simulators: camera rendering "
"and LiDAR models are functional but not photorealistic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:334
msgid ""
"Smaller ecosystem of pre-built models and environments compared to Gazebo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:335
msgid "Focused on wheeled mobile robots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Defining-Worlds-MVSim.rst:338
msgid "Further resources"
msgstr ""

